    <bibl><title>Revyen</title>,
<date when="1915-08-21">Aug. 21, 1915</date>.
<title level="a">LYNCH MOB</title><title level="a" type="sub">(Editorial)</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>There is a blot on the fair name of the United States she the State of Georgia. Yes, in an enlightened country like ours, a mob can take a prisoner out of a State penitentiary and lynch him. Yes, and is this particular came, the defendant has not get been proved guilty.</p>
   <p>Were the leaders of the mob apprehended and prosecuted." No, the authorities did not lift a finger, they ignored the entire thing.</p>
   <p>It is high time that the people pretest, and let their voices be heard. Save the good made of our fair country. It shows a decided lack of culture and Christian feeling. An anti-lynch law must be passed.</p>
